The §cIncense Altar §fused to §g§bgain a bonus(up to +300%max) to the LP gained when self-sacrificing§f.

Primal Mana is very useful to transform a few Block into other ones, it seems like having properties of an Philosopher Stone when it touches specific Blocks.
This process is very reactive so keep some distance and try to avoid touching the liquid.
Hint: As you're not finding a recipe in JEI, try to throw a bucket in a Mana Pool filled with Mana.

Our nature is one of the most beautiful things we could observe we could observe with our naked eye.
No tree looks like another and even same kinds of trees could differ in their specification.
§3Mutation is not bad in every case, as it could improve size, income, growth or simply becomes another type§f.
To get your first Leaf Blocks pollinated you'll need bees or butterflies and have vanilla saplings put into your §cPortable Analyzer (use up 1 Honey Drop for each analysis) §fto get the §5Forestry version (Oak Sapling -> Apple Oak Sapling)§f.
And in addition to see if you got a pollinated Leaf Block you need to wear §cSpectacles §for an §cApiarists' Hat(requires to be equipped in head slot)§f.
While wearing one of these, you're able to see which ones got pollinated and/or maybe gets pollinated soon (Leafs change texture).
After a successfull pollination you need to use a §cGrafter (break Leaf Block with left click) §fwhich grants you a sapling drop (even if it's not pollinated).

Hint: §cButterflies §fspawn randomly if you have §5Forestry Saplings §fgrown.
They are useful for tree pollination until having your first bees you could even collect them by right clicking it with a §cScoop §f(doesn't use up durability)

Tip: If you make a §cGreenhouse §fby simply placing a box out of glass around your tree breeding area, you could §3contain most of the butterflies in your artificial eco system§f.
Some would still glitch through, as Glass is still a transparent block (but free line to sky is required to have butterflies spawning).

Tip 2: Simple Grafters have less durability, so if you don't want to craft many of them, try out the Manasteel Grafter as soon as you have the possibility to keep an (partly) filled Mana Tablet/Band of Mana with you.

As you're progressing you might come to a point where valuable drops from Mobs are hard to gain.
Maybe a specific §cDoll §fcould be helpful to get some useful resources.
§5Hint: Enderman in a Tinkers Construct Smeltere won't teleport away if you wan't to automate early on.
The Downside is that you get less Enderpearls than killing them with a weapon enchanted with Looting.

If too much §3flux §fis built up in an area, a §cFlux Rift §fcould open up.
There is nothing you can do against it early on and this thing could really mess up your base and harm you.
Good to know, §5that it is impossible that another one opens up in an area up to 64 blocks around in each direction§f.
To get a little bit of control you could limit the height of it spawning by simply creating a solid platform above the "contaminated" area.
Some ways to reduce flux are §cTaint (which the Rift creates itself)§f,§c Crystal Farms §fand §cCondenser Lattice§f.

Hint: If you need to process much Essentia, try to spawn a Flux Rift far away from your base, as it will destroy Blocks/Machines instantly, harms you if you come too close, spawns different Thaumcraft Mobs and Taint the area around it.

§3Tip: When a rift collapses it might drops useful things, try to make a platform below it so you might get them!

Some blocks have the same §cOredictionary§f, which means they could be interchanged in some cases.
